# VENTD TEST MASTERPLAN — Coverage, Invariants, Issue Detection

**Document purpose:** This is the authoritative test-suite design for ventd. It is a companion to `ventdmasterplan.md` — every feature task in the main plan has a matching test task here, and the test plan also owns standalone test tracks that aren't tied to specific features (fuzzing, chaos, regression, supply chain). Written for Cowork to generate Claude Code prompts and review the resulting test PRs.

Relationship to the main plan: the main-plan task catalogue in §8 adds code; this plan's task catalogue in §17 adds tests. Where a feature task (e.g. `P1-HAL-01`) has a corresponding test task (`T-HAL-01`), the test task is ready only after the feature task is merged. Test tasks that are pure infrastructure (fixture libraries, CI jobs, fuzz corpora) can start in parallel with Phase 0 of the main plan.

