## 0 · Glossary

Same as main plan. Additions:

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Invariant** | A property that must always hold. Bound 1:1 to a named subtest so a regression fails at a predictable location. Example: "PWM writes are clamped to `[MinPWM, MaxPWM]`." |
| **Rule file** | A `.claude/rules/*.md` markdown file enumerating invariants. Each rule has an ID; each ID maps to exactly one subtest. |
| **Fixture** | A reusable hardware or environment mock (fake sysfs tree, stub IPMI BMC, stub USB HID device, stub WMI provider). |
| **Replay test** | A regression test named after a GitHub issue number (`TestRegression_Issue118_*`) that encodes the bug's conditions and asserts they stay fixed. |
| **Golden** | A committed reference output (YAML, JSON, diff) that tests compare against. Update via explicit `-update` flag. |
| **HIL** | Hardware-in-loop. Runs on real hardware in `validation/`. Not gating CI; gating release. |

